        cygrid, a library module for the general purpose programming
        language Python. Cygrid can be used to resample data to any
        collection of target coordinates, although its typical
        application involves FITS maps or data cubes. The FITS world
        coordinate system standard is supported. \textbackslash Methods:
        The regridding algorithm is based on the convolution of the
        original samples with a kernel of arbitrary shape. We introduce
        a lookup table scheme that allows us to parallelize the gridding
